Here is a JavaScript function that uses regex to extract the three character code "1Jn" from a given filename in the format "57-1Jn.usfm":

```javascript
function extractThreeCharCode(filename) {
  // Regex pattern to match filenames of the format "XX-THREE_CHAR_CODE.usfm"
  const pattern = /^(\d{2}-)(\w{3})\.usfm$/;

  // Test the filename against the regex pattern
  const match = filename.match(pattern);

  // If there's a match, return the three character code; otherwise, return null
  if (match) {
    return match[2];
  } else {
    return null;
  }
}

// Example usage:
const filename = "57-1Jn.usfm";
console.log(extractThreeCharCode(filename)); // Output: 1Jn
```

This function will work for filenames in the specified format, where the three character code can be upper or lower case letters or digits. The function returns the extracted three character code if found, otherwise it returns null.
